{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SrpMYv6NtGVYTFnnBsWgiK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup. I need to:\n\n1. Create a MinIO Service so it's accessible at `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000`\n2. Get the Elastic password to authenticate with ES\n3. Create the `es-secure-settings` secret with the S3/MinIO credentials in the keystore format\n4. Configure each Elasticsearch pod's keystore with the MinIO credentials\n5. Reload the secure settings (or restart pods if needed)\n6. Register a snapshot repository named \"minio-repo\"\n7. Create a snapshot\n\nThe key challenge here is that Elasticsearch secure settings (keystore) need to be configured in each node. \n\nFor Kubernetes deployments, I have a few options: manually adding credentials to the keystore in each pod, using an init container to mount a pre-built keystore from a secret, or leveraging the `_reload_secure_settings` API if the keystore already contains the settings. The cleanest approach for this setup is to use an init container that builds the keystore with the MinIO credentials before Elasticsearch starts.\n\nNow I need to check what plugins are currently installed and whether the S3 repository plugin is available.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2933,"cache_read_input_tokens":31472,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2933},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"82476b60-f4cb-48ca-92a0-0e5d08c71292","uuid":"7eaa7024-6211-4582-b080-39520ac21abc","request_id":"req_011CcQgZE7GjQB5uu27vmYuJ"}
