{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FkghtQ9iwVUufqWBGjfmzM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**What was configured:**\n\n1. **MinIO Service** (`minio`) created so `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000` resolves — this was missing and caused the init job to fail.\n\n2. **`es-backups` bucket** created in MinIO (the init job had failed without the service).\n\n3. **`es-secure-settings` Secret** created with `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` (values: `minioadmin`). Credentials are stored only in this Secret — not in `elasticsearch.yml` or env vars.\n\n4. **Keystore configured on all 8 cluster nodes:**\n   - `elasticsearch` StatefulSet: patched with a `keystore-init` init container that reads from `es-secure-settings` Secret, copies config files, and runs `elasticsearch-keystore add` — avoids running the JVM keystore tool in memory-constrained running pods.\n   - `es-cluster` StatefulSet: credentials added directly via exec (2Gi memory pods tolerate the JVM).\n   - `es-data-new` StatefulSet: same init container pattern applied.\n\n5. **`POST /_nodes/reload_secure_settings`** called — all 8 nodes confirmed updated (`total:8, successful:8`).\n\n6. **`minio-repo`** snapshot repository registered as type `s3`, pointing to `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000`, bucket `es-backups`, HTTP protocol with path-style access.\n\n7. **`snapshot-1`** created — `state: SUCCESS`, 10/10 shards, snapshot files confirmed in MinIO bucket."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1076,"cache_read_input_tokens":157746,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1076},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":n